—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/source.mdЩ@bc44df1759c67abc0d9c63bf53d0b7c190e588e9f80cfbe2e806d692a286c704­title: source‘ЁExamplesЪшRuns foo.nu in the current context.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> source foo.nu


```
Runs foo.nu in current context and call the command defined, suppose foo.nu has content: 
``def say-hi [] { echo 'Hi!' }``
.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> source ./foo.nu; say-hi


```
Sourcing 
``null``
 is a no-op.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> source null


```
Source can be used with const variables.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> const file = if $nu.is-interactive { "interactive.nu" } else { null }; source $file


```
